                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14477594" author="paulk" created="Fri, 16 Nov 2007 08:35:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am sure people are aware of the Bamboo 1.4 build failing but because we are so close to the next release, just adding this here so it doesn&apos;t get lost.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14463597" author="ait" created="Sat, 17 Nov 2007 05:49:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You are right. I will rewrite it right now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14463667" author="paulk" created="Sat, 17 Nov 2007 06:58:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Maybe also a TODO comment  to go back to Java 1.5 method once we move to Java 1.5&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14463567" author="blackdrag" created="Sat, 17 Nov 2007 11:54:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;well, Ylex code is a bit more complex than needed in this case, since the path is &quot;slashified&quot; before which means that it will contain no &quot;\&quot;, only &quot;/&quot;. Which means it is save to simply put the String in \\Q&lt;br class=&quot;atl-forced-newline&quot; /&gt;E, because no &lt;br class=&quot;atl-forced-newline&quot; /&gt; will be inside the string. So if we say we simplify it in that way, then there is really no need to call that method.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14477591" author="paulk" created="Thu, 22 Nov 2007 05:32:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
